To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Florida Sunshine Law, I hereby request the following records:

Any and all electronic communication pertaining to the alleged "trespass" at Bear Creek Bridge by the names of Dan Curry, Daniel Lee Curry or Daniel L Curry.

Please include any email or text message exchanges between any county employees including but not limited to county commissioners, county commissioner aids or department head and any member(s) of the sheriff department.

Please include a copy of any arrest warrant(s) and any correspondence regarding the arrest warrant.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Chase Galloway

title: Law Enforcement Agencies accessing statewide LexisNexis/West Accurint database

communications.subject: Rhode Island Access to Public Records Act Request: Law Enforcement Agencies accessing statewide LexisNexis/West Accurint database
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Rhode Island Access to Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

I am seeking any agreements, documents, reports, communications, lists, logs or datasets showing the names of the state and local law enforcement agencies that have bought or can use Accurint Databases through the statewide contract MPA 280, Legal Subscriptions,  LexisNexis Risk Solutions FL Inc., and West Publishing Corporation.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Paul Tepper
